gov.va.med.srcalc.domain.model

Class DiscreteNumericalVariable

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.va.med.srcalc.domain.model.AbstractVariable
      • gov.va.med.srcalc.domain.model.AbstractNumericalVariable
        • gov.va.med.srcalc.domain.model.DiscreteNumericalVariable
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DiscreteVariable, Variable

    @Entity
public final class DiscreteNumericalVariable
extends AbstractNumericalVariable
implements DiscreteVariable

    A Variable that ultimately represents one of a finite, discrete set of values. This is mainly useful for a lab results (e.g., White Blood Count <= 11.0x1000/mm^3 or > 11.0x100/mm^3), but may be used for other numerical values such as Body Mass Index.

    Per Effective Java Item 17, this class is marked final because it was not designed for inheritance.
